\h GLOSSARY \d

Asleep
This is an IC ("In-Character") term for the state of being logged out.

Awake
This is an IC ("In-Character") term for the state of being logged in.

In-Character
Something said or done as a character, in the context of role-playing. Or, in the context of the virtual world.

Interactive Non-Player Character
A character that is usually controlled by the server, and sometimes controlled, or otherwise actively managed, by the administrators.

Mobile
A non-player character. Sometimes abbreviated to "mob."

Multi-Playing
When a single player simultaneously plays with multiple characters.

Multi-User Dungeon
This generally refers to a (usually text-based) virtual world in its totality.

Newbie
A player who is new to CurryMUD.

Non-Player Character
A character controlled by the server. A "mobile."

Out-Of-Character
Something said or done as a player, outside the context of role-playing. Or, outside the context of the virtual world.

Permadeath
When a player character dies, it is truly dead; a deceased player character cannot return to the virtual world in any way, shape, or form.

Player Character
A character controlled by a human player.

Player Killing
When one player character kills another player character.

Player vs. Player
When one player character attacks another player character.

Role-play Enforced

Role-playing

Room
